H0.text: Inhibitor, malonate plays a negative role on the enzyme succinate dehydrogenase.

H1.text: Catalyst is the negative role that malonate plays on the enzyme succinate dehydrogenase.

H2.text: Pathway is the negative role that malonate plays on the enzyme succinate dehydrogenase.

H3.text: Receptor is the negative role that malonate plays on the enzyme succinate dehydrogenase.

A4.text: Succinate-analogue inhibitors include the synthetic compound malonate as well as the TCA cycle intermediates, malate and oxaloacetate.

A5.text: Indeed, oxaloacetate is one of the most potent inhibitors of Complex II.
